Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%grams}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, stir in the garlic and fry for ~{30%secs}. Add in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @Butter{30%grams} until melted. Simmer until the sauce is thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

Add the @Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta{250%grams} and broccoli. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Ciabatta ==

If you don't have a #toaster{}, preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the @Ciabatta{1}(halved).

If you're using the toaster, toast the ciabatta in your toaster until golden. If you're using the oven, pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once toasted, drizzle some @olive oil{drizzle} over the ciabatta.

== Finish ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} and cook for ~{1-2%mins}.

Add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} to the pan. Gently stir to melt the cheese and combine everything together.

Share your creamy garlic butter pasta between your #serving plates{}. Serve with your toasted ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!